Characters

Warning this page contains spoliers.

This page contains almost all the information you need about the characters in the weird world of Gravity Falls.

Dipper Pines

Dipper Pines is an adventurous twelve-year-old boy who is obsessed with Journal 3 and finding the author of it. Though he may not be the manliness guy he's still a kind, honest, and brave brother. Surprisingly, Dipper isn't his real name, it's just a nickname because of the birthmark on his forehead that looks like the Big Dipper. But what the show never reveals is his real name which is Mason.

Dipper's twins with Mabel and great of nephew Stan and Ford. His closest friends are Soos and Wendy and he has a not so secret crush on her as well.

Dipper is voiced by Jason Ritter.

Mabel Pines

Mabel is a sweet and creative twelve-year-old girl. Although she can be annoying and a little demanding, she's supportive to everyone she knows. Her artistic skills take her far, from her sweater knitting to making wax sculptures there's no stopping this creative child.

Mabel's twins with Dipper and great niece of Stan and Ford. Her best friends are Candy and Grenda and she has a whole tone of crushes over the summer.

Mabel is voiced by Kristen Schaal.

Grunkle Stan

The owner of the Mystery Shack and scam master he's Stan Pines. Everyone in Gravity Falls seems to know him but do they realy know this secretive man. This 58-year-old may seem strict and mean but he's actually fun and chill. As the scam artist he is he'll do almost anything to get his hands on some money.

Stan is great unckle of Dipper and Mabel and twins with Ford. He's the boss of Wendy, Soos, Dipper, and Mabel.

Stan is voiced by Alex Hirsch.

Soos Ramirez

Soos is a lovable guy who will do anything for the Pines family. This 22-year-old man-child loves to go on adventures with Dipper and Mabel. His overall dream is to take on Stan's job of being Mr. Mystery one day.

Soos is the grandson of Abuelita and sees Stan as a father figure.

Soos is also voiced by Alex Hirsch.

Wendy Corduroy

This 15-year-old loves hanging out with Dipper and Mabel and going on adventures with them. She also likes to hang out with Tambry, Lee, Nate, Robbie, and Thompson. Even though she doesn't like to work, her time working this summer when Dipper and Mabel came along made it a blast.

Wendy is the only daughter to Manly Dan and sister to her three brothers Marcus, Kevin, and Gus.

Wendy is voiced by Linda Cardellini.

Gideon Gleeful

Gideon is a ten-year-old boy and he's bossy. He takes what he wants, like Mabel in "The Hand That Rocks Mabel." He also attempted to take the Mystery Shack twice. Gideon only takes what he's obsessed with like his crush on Mabel or his desire for power from all the Journals. The sad thing is he even bosses his parents around.

Gideon is son to Bud and Mrs. Gleeful.

Gideon is voiced by Thurop Van Orman.

Pacifica Northwest

Pacifica is daughter to Preston and Priscilla Northwest.

Pacifica is voiced by Jackie Buscarino.

Robbie Valentino

Robbie is what you'd call the "goth guy." He can be depressed at times and also a jerk, but that doesn't stop him from impressing who he likes. It was harder for him to do so once he met Dipper. Dipper is his arch-enemy, because when he dated Wendy he saw that Dipper got jelous of him.

Robbie is son to Greg and Janice Valentino. He's dateing Tambry and his ex-girlfriend is Wendy.

Robbie is voiced by T.J. Miller.

Old Man McGucket

This old kook is a lot smarter then people think. Fiddleford McGucket may seem crazy, but he's had a complicated life. In "Society of the Blind Eye" it becomes known that McGucket worked with the author and hated what he had seen. This effected him so badly, he became the weird kook we all know.

McGucket is the father of Tate.

McGucket is voiced by Alex Hirsch.

The Author

The Author is reavealed in "Not What He Seems" to be Ford Pines, Stan's twin brother. Ford has always felt like the odd one out because of the six figers he has on each hand. But that didn't stop him from his reaserch on science and paranormal activity. Soon, after finding Gravity Falls' paranormal activity, he became too obsessed with it he didn't realize how dangourus it could be.

Ford is twins with Stan and great uncle to Dipper and Mabel.

Ford is voiced by J. K. Simmons.

Bill Cipher

Bill Cipher is an imortal demon who is said to have destroyed his home demention. Since then, he's wanted to get his hands on Gravity Falls and the whole world. In order for him to acomplish this, he's been using his mind games and trickery to get someone to let him into their demention.

Bill is voiced by Alex Hirsch as well.
